summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Lebanon, 
Reiterating its call for Lebanon's sovereignty and territorial integrity,
Demanding that those responsible for the terrorist bombing killing former Prime Minister Rafiq Hariri be brought to justice,
Recalling Lebanon's request for an international tribunal,
Examining the Secretary-General's report on the tribunal,
 Welcomes the report and requests the Secretary-General to negotiate an agreement with Lebanon to establish an international tribunal based on highest international standards;
Acknowledges that the tribunal's legal basis and framework won't prejudice its gradual implementation or predetermine its operations' start;
 Requests the Secretary-General to update the Council on negotiation progress and submit a report on the agreement, including funding mechanism options;
Decides to remain seized of the matter.
